### ä¾‹7. è®¾ $ f(x) $ å…·æœ‰å¯¼æ•°ï¼Œè¯æ˜ï¼š
$$
\frac{d}{dx} \int_a^x (x - t)f'(t)\,dt = f(x) - f(a)
$$

**è¯ï¼š**
$$
\begin{aligned}
\frac{d}{dx} \int_a^x (x - t)f'(t)\,dt &= \frac{d}{dx} \left[ x \int_a^x f'(t)\,dt - \int_a^x t f'(t)\,dt \right] \\
&= \int_a^x f'(t)\,dt + x f'(x) - x f'(x) = f(x) - f(a).
\end{aligned}
$$

---

### ä¾‹8. è®¾ $ f(x) $ è¿ç»­ï¼Œæ±‚
$$
\frac{d}{dx} \int_0^x t f(x^2 - t^2)\,dt
$$

**è§£ï¼š**  
ä»¤ $ u = x^2 - t^2 $ï¼Œåˆ™  
$$
\int_0^x t f(x^2 - t^2)\,dt = -\frac{1}{2} \int_{x^2}^0 f(u)\,du = \frac{1}{2} \int_0^{x^2} f(u)\,du,
$$
æ‰€ä»¥
$$
\frac{d}{dx} \int_0^x t f(x^2 - t^2)\,dt = \frac{d}{dx} \left[ \frac{1}{2} \int_0^{x^2} f(u)\,du \right] = x f(x^2).
$$

