### ä¾‹9. è®¾
$$
f(x) = \int_0^x \left( \int_1^{\sin t} \sqrt{1 + u^4}\,du \right) dt,
$$
æ±‚ $ f''(x) $ã€‚

**è§£ï¼š**  
å…ˆç”¨åˆ†éƒ¨ç§¯åˆ†æ³•åŒ–ç®€ï¼š
$$
\begin{aligned}
f(x) &= \left[ t \int_1^{\sin t} \sqrt{1 + u^4}\,du \right]_0^x - \int_0^x t \cdot \frac{d}{dt} \left( \int_1^{\sin t} \sqrt{1 + u^4}\,du \right) dt \\
&= x \int_1^{\sin x} \sqrt{1 + u^4}\,du - \int_0^x t \cdot \sqrt{1 + \sin^4 t} \cdot \cos t\,dt.
\end{aligned}
$$

äºæ˜¯
$$
f'(x) = \int_1^{\sin x} \sqrt{1 + u^4}\,du + x \cdot \sqrt{1 + \sin^4 x} \cdot \cos x - x \sqrt{1 + \sin^4 x} \cos x,
$$
å³
$$
f'(x) = \int_1^{\sin x} \sqrt{1 + u^4}\,du.
$$

å†æ±‚å¯¼å¾—
$$
f''(x) = \sqrt{1 + \sin^4 x} \cdot \cos x.
