### ä¾‹2. è®¾
$$
f(x) = 3x - \sqrt{1 - x^2} \int_0^1 f^2(x)\,dx,
$$
æ±‚ $ f(x) $ã€‚

**è§£ï¼š**  
ä»¤ $ A = \int_0^1 f^2(x)\,dx $ï¼Œç”±å·²çŸ¥å¾—
$$
f(x) = 3x - A \sqrt{1 - x^2},
$$
å› æ­¤
$$
f^2(x) = \left(3x - A \sqrt{1 - x^2}\right)^2 = 9x^2 - 6A x \sqrt{1 - x^2} + A^2 (1 - x^2).
$$

ä»£å…¥ç§¯åˆ†ï¼š
$$
A = \int_0^1 f^2(x)\,dx = \int_0^1 \left[9x^2 - 6A x \sqrt{1 - x^2} + A^2 (1 - x^2)\right]\,dx
$$

é€é¡¹è®¡ç®—ï¼š
- $ \int_0^1 9x^2\,dx = 3 $
- $ \int_0^1 -6A x \sqrt{1 - x^2}\,dx = 6A \cdot \frac{1}{3} = 2A $ ï¼ˆä»¤ $ u = 1 - x^2 $ï¼‰
- $ \int_0^1 A^2 (1 - x^2)\,dx = A^2 \left(1 - \frac{1}{3}\right) = \frac{2}{3} A^2 $

æ‰€ä»¥
$$
A = 3 - 2A + \frac{2}{3} A^2
\Rightarrow \frac{2}{3} A^2 - 3A + 3 = 0
\Rightarrow 2A^2 - 9A + 9 = 0
\Rightarrow A = 3 \quad \text{æˆ–} \quad A = \frac{3}{2}.
$$

ä»£å›å¾—ï¼š
$$
f(x) = 3x - 3\sqrt{1 - x^2} \quad \text{æˆ–} \quad f(x) = 3x - \frac{3}{2} \sqrt{1 - x^2}.
$$

