## ä¾‹7  
è®¾  
$$
f(x) = 
\begin{cases}
1 + x^2, & x \leq 0 \\
e^{-x}, & x > 0
\end{cases}
$$  
æ±‚  
$$
\int_1^3 f(x - 2)\,dx.
$$

### è§£  
ä»¤ $ x - 2 = t $ï¼Œåˆ™ $ dx = dt $ã€‚  
å½“ $ x = 1 $ æ—¶ï¼Œ$ t = -1 $ï¼›å½“ $ x = 3 $ æ—¶ï¼Œ$ t = 1 $ã€‚äºæ˜¯  
$$
\int_1^3 f(x - 2)\,dx = \int_{-1}^1 f(t)\,dt = \int_{-1}^0 (1 + t^2)\,dt + \int_0^1 e^{-t}\,dt
$$
$$
= \left[ t + \frac{1}{3}t^3 \right]_{-1}^0 - \left[ e^{-t} \right]_0^1 = \left(0 - (-1 + \frac{-1}{3})\right) - (e^{-1} - 1)
= 1 + \frac{1}{3} - \frac{1}{e} = \frac{7}{3} - \frac{1}{e}.
$$

---

## ä¾‹8  
è®¾ $ f'(x) = \arcsin((x - 1)^2) $ï¼Œ$ f(0) = 0 $ï¼Œæ±‚  
$$
\int_0^1 f(x)\,dx.
$$

### è§£  
ç”¨åˆ†éƒ¨ç§¯åˆ†æ³•ï¼š  
$$
\int_0^1 f(x)\,dx = \int_0^1 f(x)\,d(x - 1) = (x - 1)f(x)\Big|_0^1 - \int_0^1 (x - 1)\,df(x)
$$
$$
= -\int_0^1 (x - 1)f'(x)\,dx = -\int_0^1 (x - 1)\arcsin((x - 1)^2)\,dx
$$
ä»¤ $ u = (x - 1)^2 $ï¼Œåˆ™ $ du = 2(x - 1)\,dx $ï¼Œå³ $ (x - 1)\,dx = \frac{1}{2}du $ï¼Œä¸”å½“ $ x = 0 $ æ—¶ $ u = 1 $ï¼Œ$ x = 1 $ æ—¶ $ u = 0 $ï¼Œæ‰€ä»¥  
$$
= -\int_1^0 \arcsin u \cdot \frac{1}{2}du = \frac{1}{2}\int_0^1 \arcsin u\,du
$$
ä½¿ç”¨åˆ†éƒ¨ç§¯åˆ†ï¼š  
$$
= \frac{1}{2}\left[ u\arcsin u \Big|_0^1 - \int_0^1 \frac{u}{\sqrt{1 - u^2}}\,du \right]
= \frac{1}{2}\left[ \frac{\pi}{2} - \int_0^1 \frac{u}{\sqrt{1 - u^2}}\,du \right]
$$
ä»¤ $ v = 1 - u^2 $ï¼Œ$ dv = -2u\,du $ï¼Œå¾—  
$$
\int_0^1 \frac{u}{\sqrt{1 - u^2}}\,du = \frac{1}{2}\int_0^1 v^{-1/2}dv = \frac{1}{2} \cdot 2 = 1
$$
æ‰€ä»¥  
$$
\int_0^1 f(x)\,dx = \frac{1}{2}\left( \frac{\pi}{2} - 1 \right) = \frac{\pi}{4} - \frac{1}{2}.
$$

> âœ… æœ€ç»ˆç»“æœä¸ºï¼š  
> $$
> \boxed{\frac{\pi}{4} - \frac{1}{2}}
> $$

