## é¢˜å‹å››ï¼šæ¶‰åŠå˜é™ç§¯åˆ†çš„é—®é¢˜

### ä¾‹11  
è®¡ç®—  
$$
\int_0^1 \frac{f(x)}{\sqrt{x}}\,dx,
\quad \text{å…¶ä¸­ } f(x) = \int_1^x \frac{\ln(t+1)}{t}\,dt.
$$

### è§£  
ç”±å·²çŸ¥ï¼š  
$$
f(1) = 0,\quad f'(x) = \frac{\ln(x+1)}{x}
$$
åŸå¼å˜ä¸ºï¼š  
$$
\int_0^1 \frac{f(x)}{\sqrt{x}}\,dx = 2\int_0^1 f(x)\,d(\sqrt{x}) = 2\left[ f(x)\sqrt{x} \Big|_0^1 - \int_0^1 f'(x)\sqrt{x}\,dx \right]
$$
$$
= 2\left[ f(1)\cdot1 - \int_0^1 \frac{\ln(x+1)}{x} \cdot \sqrt{x}\,dx \right] = -2\int_0^1 \ln(x+1)\cdot x^{-1/2}\,dx
$$
$$
= -4\int_0^1 \ln(x+1)\,d(\sqrt{x}) = -4\left[ \ln(x+1)\cdot\sqrt{x} \Big|_0^1 - \int_0^1 \frac{1}{x+1} \cdot \sqrt{x}\,dx \right]
$$
$$
= -4\left[ \ln 2 - \int_0^1 \frac{\sqrt{x}}{x+1}\,dx \right]
$$
ä»¤ $ u = \sqrt{x} $ï¼Œåˆ™ $ x = u^2 $ï¼Œ$ dx = 2u\,du $ï¼Œå¾—  
$$
\int_0^1 \frac{\sqrt{x}}{x+1}\,dx = \int_0^1 \frac{u}{u^2 + 1} \cdot 2u\,du = 2\int_0^1 \frac{u^2}{u^2 + 1}\,du = 2\int_0^1 \left(1 - \frac{1}{u^2 + 1}\right)du
= 2\left[ u - \arctan u \right]_0^1 = 2(1 - \frac{\pi}{4})
$$
ä»£å…¥å¾—ï¼š  
$$
= -4\left[ \ln 2 - 2(1 - \frac{\pi}{4}) \right] = -4\ln 2 + 8 - 2\pi
$$

> âœ… ç»“æœä¸ºï¼š  
> $$
> \boxed{8 - 2\pi - 4\ln 2}
> $$

### è¯„æ³¨  
è¢«ç§¯å‡½æ•°ä¸­å«æœ‰å˜é™ç§¯åˆ†ï¼Œä¸€èˆ¬å¯ç”¨åˆ†éƒ¨ç§¯åˆ†æ³•ã€‚

---

### ä¾‹12  
è®¾ $ f(x) $ è¿ç»­ï¼Œä¸”  
$$
\int_0^x t f(2x - t)\,dt = \frac{1}{2} \arctan x^2,
\quad f(1) = 1,
$$  
æ±‚  
$$
\int_1^2 f(x)\,dx.
$$

### è§£  
ä»¤ $ u = 2x - t $ï¼Œåˆ™ $ t = 2x - u $ï¼Œ$ dt = -du $ï¼Œå½“ $ t = 0 $ æ—¶ $ u = 2x $ï¼Œ$ t = x $ æ—¶ $ u = x $ï¼Œæ‰€ä»¥  
$$
\int_0^x t f(2x - t)\,dt = \int_{2x}^x (2x - u)f(u)(-du) = \int_x^{2x} (2x - u)f(u)\,du
= 2x \int_x^{2x} f(u)\,du - \int_x^{2x} u f(u)\,du
$$
å› æ­¤  
$$
2x \int_x^{2x} f(u)\,du - \int_x^{2x} u f(u)\,du = \frac{1}{2} \arctan x^2
$$
ä¸¤è¾¹å¯¹ $ x $ æ±‚å¯¼ï¼š  
å·¦è¾¹ï¼š  
$$
2\int_x^{2x} f(u)\,du + 2x \left[2f(2x) - f(x)\right] - \left[2x f(2x) - x f(x)\right]
= 2\int_x^{2x} f(u)\,du + 4x f(2x) - 2x f(x) - 2x f(2x) + x f(x)
= 2\int_x^{2x} f(u)\,du + 2x f(2x) - x f(x)
$$
å³è¾¹å¯¼æ•°ä¸ºï¼š  
$$
\frac{1}{2} \cdot \frac{2x}{1 + x^4} = \frac{x}{1 + x^4}
$$
æ‰€ä»¥  
$$
2\int_x^{2x} f(u)\,du + 2x f(2x) - x f(x) = \frac{x}{1 + x^4}
\Rightarrow 2\int_x^{2x} f(u)\,du = \frac{x}{1 + x^4} + x f(x)
$$
ä»¤ $ x = 1 $ï¼š  
$$
2\int_1^2 f(u)\,du = \frac{1}{2} + 1 \cdot f(1) = \frac{1}{2} + 1 = \frac{3}{2}
\Rightarrow \int_1^2 f(x)\,dx = \frac{3}{4}
$$

> âœ… ç»“æœä¸ºï¼š  
> $$
> \boxed{\frac{3}{4}}
> $$

