#### ä¾‹22  
è®¾ $ f(x) $ æ˜¯ $[0,1]$ ä¸Šçš„è¿ç»­éè´Ÿå•è°ƒå‡å‡½æ•°ï¼Œè¯æ˜ï¼šå¯¹äº $ 0 < \alpha < \beta \leq 1 $ï¼Œæœ‰  
$$
\int_0^\alpha f(x)\,dx \geq \frac{\alpha}{\beta} \int_\alpha^\beta f(x)\,dx.
$$

### è¯  
ç”±ç§¯åˆ†ä¸­å€¼å®šç†ï¼Œå­˜åœ¨ $ \xi_1 \in [0, \alpha] $ï¼Œ$ \xi_2 \in [\alpha, \beta] $ï¼Œä½¿å¾—  
$$
\int_0^\alpha f(x)\,dx = \alpha f(\xi_1), \quad \int_\alpha^\beta f(x)\,dx = (\beta - \alpha)f(\xi_2),
\quad (0 \leq \xi_1 \leq \alpha \leq \xi_2 \leq \beta).
$$

ç”±äº $ f(x) $ éè´Ÿä¸”å•è°ƒé€’å‡ï¼Œæœ‰ $ \xi_1 \leq \xi_2 \Rightarrow f(\xi_1) \geq f(\xi_2) $ï¼Œæ‰€ä»¥  
$$
\alpha f(\xi_1) \geq \alpha f(\xi_2) \geq \frac{\alpha}{\beta} (\beta - \alpha) f(\xi_2) = \frac{\alpha}{\beta} \int_\alpha^\beta f(x)\,dx.
$$

å³  
$$
\int_0^\alpha f(x)\,dx \geq \frac{\alpha}{\beta} \int_\alpha^\beta f(x)\,dx.
$$

> âœ… å¾—è¯


### ä¹ é¢˜ 24  
è®¾ $f'(x)$ æ˜¯è¿ç»­å‡½æ•°ï¼Œå®šä¹‰  
$$
F(x) = \int_0^x f(t)f'(2a - t) dt
$$  
è¯æ˜ï¼š  
$$
F(2a) - 2F(a) = f^2(a) - f(0)f(2a)
$$

**è¯**  
$$
F(2a) - 2F(a) = \int_0^{2a} f(t)f'(2a - t) dt - 2 \int_0^a f(t)f'(2a - t) dt
$$

$$
= \int_a^{2a} f(t)f'(2a - t) dt - \underbrace{\int_0^a f(t)f'(2a - t) dt}_{\text{è®°ä½œ } I}
$$

è€ƒè™‘ï¼š
$$
\int_a^{2a} f(t)f'(2a - t) dt = -\int_a^{2a} f(t) d(f(2a - t))
$$

$$
= -f(t)f(2a - t)\Big|_a^{2a} + \int_a^{2a} f'(t)f(2a - t) dt
= -[f(2a)f(0) - f(a)f(a)] + \int_a^{2a} f'(t)f(2a - t) dt
$$

$$
= f^2(a) - f(0)f(2a) + \int_a^{2a} f'(t)f(2a - t) dt
$$

ä»¤ $u = 2a - t$ï¼Œåˆ™å½“ $t = a$ æ—¶ $u = a$ï¼Œ$t = 2a$ æ—¶ $u = 0$ï¼Œä¸” $dt = -du$ï¼š

$$
\int_a^{2a} f'(t)f(2a - t) dt = \int_a^0 f'(2a - u)f(u)(-du) = \int_0^a f'(2a - u)f(u) du
$$

æœ€ç»ˆå¾—åˆ°ï¼š
$$
F(2a) - 2F(a) = f^2(a) - f(0)f(2a)
$$

