## é¢˜å‹ä¹ï¼šåå¸¸ç§¯åˆ†çš„è®¡ç®—

### ä¾‹28. æ±‚ $\displaystyle \int_1^{+\infty} \frac{\arctan x}{x^2} dx$

**æç¤º**  
- æ–¹æ³•ä¸€ï¼šåˆ†éƒ¨ç§¯åˆ†æ³•  
- æ–¹æ³•äºŒï¼šä½œå˜æ¢ $\arctan x = t$ï¼Œå†ç”¨åˆ†éƒ¨ç§¯åˆ†æ³•  

**ç­”æ¡ˆ**ï¼š$\displaystyle \frac{\pi}{4} + \frac{1}{2} \ln 2$

---

### ä¾‹29. è¯æ˜  
$$
\int_0^{+\infty} \frac{1}{1+x^4} dx = \int_0^{+\infty} \frac{x^2}{1+x^4} dx = \frac{\pi}{2\sqrt{2}}
$$

**è¯**  
ä»¤ $x = \dfrac{1}{t}$ï¼Œåˆ™  
$$
\int_0^{+\infty} \frac{1}{1+x^4} dx = \int_0^{+\infty} \frac{t^2}{1+t^4} dt = \int_0^{+\infty} \frac{x^2}{1+x^4} dx
$$

ä»è€Œ  
$$
\int_0^{+\infty} \frac{1}{1+x^4} dx = \frac{1}{2} \int_0^{+\infty} \frac{1+x^2}{1+x^4} dx = \frac{1}{2} \int_0^{+\infty} \frac{\frac{1}{x^2}+1}{x^2 + \frac{1}{x^2}} dx
$$

$$
= \frac{1}{2} \int_0^{+\infty} \frac{1}{\left(x - \frac{1}{x}\right)^2 + 2} d\left(x - \frac{1}{x}\right)
= \frac{1}{2\sqrt{2}} \arctan\left(\frac{x}{\sqrt{2}} - \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}x}\right)\Big|_0^{+\infty}
= \frac{\pi}{2\sqrt{2}}
$$

---

### ä¾‹30. è®¡ç®—  
$$
\int_{-1}^{1} \frac{2x^2 + x\cos x}{1 + \sqrt{1 - x^2}} dx
$$

**è§£**  
åŸå¼æ‹†åˆ†ä¸ºï¼š
$$
= \int_{-1}^{1} \frac{2x^2}{1 + \sqrt{1 - x^2}} dx + \int_{-1}^{1} \frac{x\cos x}{1 + \sqrt{1 - x^2}} dx
$$

- ç¬¬ä¸€é¡¹æ˜¯ **å¶å‡½æ•°**ï¼Œç¬¬äºŒé¡¹æ˜¯ **å¥‡å‡½æ•°**ï¼Œæ•…ç¬¬äºŒé¡¹ç§¯åˆ†ä¸º 0ã€‚

$$
= 2 \int_0^{1} \frac{2x^2}{1 + \sqrt{1 - x^2}} dx = 4 \int_0^{1} \frac{x^2}{1 + \sqrt{1 - x^2}} dx
$$

å¯¹åˆ†æ¯æœ‰ç†åŒ–ï¼š
$$
= 4 \int_0^{1} \frac{x^2 (1 - \sqrt{1 - x^2})}{1 - (1 - x^2)} dx = 4 \int_0^{1} x^2 (1 - \sqrt{1 - x^2}) dx
$$

$$
= 4 \int_0^{1} (1 - \sqrt{1 - x^2}) dx = 4 - 4 \int_0^{1} \sqrt{1 - x^2} dx
$$

å…¶ä¸­ $\displaystyle \int_0^{1} \sqrt{1 - x^2} dx$ æ˜¯å•ä½åœ†åœ¨ç¬¬ä¸€è±¡é™çš„é¢ç§¯ï¼Œå³ $\dfrac{\pi}{4}$ã€‚

$$
= 4 - 4 \cdot \frac{\pi}{4} = 4 - \pi
$$

> ğŸ’¡ æ³¨ï¼šåˆ©ç”¨å®šç§¯åˆ†çš„å‡ ä½•æ„ä¹‰ç®€åŒ–è®¡ç®—ã€‚

---

### è¯¾å ‚ç»ƒä¹  1  
è®¾å‡½æ•° $\varphi(x)$ æ»¡è¶³ $\varphi'(x) = \arctan(x-1)^2$ï¼Œä¸” $\varphi(0) = 0$ï¼Œæ±‚ï¼š
$$
I = \int_0^1 \varphi(x) dx
$$

**è§£**  
ä½¿ç”¨åˆ†éƒ¨ç§¯åˆ†ï¼š
$$
I = (x-1)\varphi(x)\Big|_0^1 - \int_0^1 (x-1)\varphi'(x) dx
= \int_0^1 (1 - x)\arctan(x-1)^2 dx
$$

ä»¤ $u = 1 - x$ï¼Œåˆ™ï¼š
$$
= \int_0^1 u \arctan u^2 du
= \left[\frac{u^2}{2} \arctan u^2\right]_0^1 - \int_0^1 \frac{u^3}{1 + u^4} du
= \frac{\pi}{8} - \frac{1}{4} \ln 2
$$

