## 4ï¼šè¯æ˜ç­‰å¼

**é¢˜ç›®**  
è¯æ˜ï¼š
$$
\int_1^a f\left(x^2 + \frac{a^2}{x^2}\right) \frac{dx}{x} = \int_1^a f\left(x + \frac{a^2}{x}\right) \frac{dx}{x}
$$

**è¯**  
å¯¹ç­‰å¼å·¦è¾¹ä½œå˜é‡ä»£æ¢ $ t = x^2 $ï¼Œåˆ™ $ dt = 2x\,dx $ï¼Œå³ $ dx = \dfrac{dt}{2x} $

å½“ $ x = 1 $ æ—¶ï¼Œ$ t = 1 $ï¼›å½“ $ x = a $ æ—¶ï¼Œ$ t = a^2 $

$$
\int_1^a f\left(x^2 + \frac{a^2}{x^2}\right) \frac{dx}{x} = \int_1^{a^2} f\left(t + \frac{a^2}{t}\right) \frac{1}{2} \cdot \frac{dt}{t}
= \frac{1}{2} \int_1^{a^2} f\left(t + \frac{a^2}{t}\right) \frac{dt}{t}
$$

æ‹†åˆ†ä¸ºä¸¤éƒ¨åˆ†ï¼š
$$
= \frac{1}{2} \left[ \int_1^a f\left(t + \frac{a^2}{t}\right) \frac{dt}{t} + \int_a^{a^2} f\left(t + \frac{a^2}{t}\right) \frac{dt}{t} \right]
$$

å¯¹ç¬¬äºŒé¡¹ä½œä»£æ¢ $ u = \dfrac{a^2}{t} $ï¼Œåˆ™ $ t = \dfrac{a^2}{u} $ï¼Œ$ dt = -\dfrac{a^2}{u^2} du $

å½“ $ t = a $ æ—¶ï¼Œ$ u = a $ï¼›å½“ $ t = a^2 $ æ—¶ï¼Œ$ u = 1 $

$$
\int_a^{a^2} f\left(t + \frac{a^2}{t}\right) \frac{dt}{t} = \int_a^1 f\left(\frac{a^2}{u} + u\right) \frac{-\frac{a^2}{u^2} du}{\frac{a^2}{u}} = \int_1^a f\left(u + \frac{a^2}{u}\right) \frac{du}{u}
$$

ä»£å…¥åŸå¼å¾—ï¼š
$$
\frac{1}{2} \left[ \int_1^a f\left(t + \frac{a^2}{t}\right) \frac{dt}{t} + \int_1^a f\left(u + \frac{a^2}{u}\right) \frac{du}{u} \right] = \int_1^a f\left(x + \frac{a^2}{x}\right) \frac{dx}{x}
$$

æ•…åŸç­‰å¼æˆç«‹ã€‚$\square$

---

## 5ï¼šæ—‹è½¬ä½“ä½“ç§¯è®¡ç®—

**é¢˜ç›®**  
æ±‚æ›²çº¿ $ y = 3(1 - x^2) $ ä¸ $ x $ è½´å›´æˆçš„å°é—­å›¾å½¢ç»•ç›´çº¿ $ y = 3 $ æ—‹è½¬ä¸€å‘¨æ‰€å¾—çš„æ—‹è½¬ä½“ä½“ç§¯ã€‚

**è§£**  
åˆ©ç”¨â€œåœ†ç¯æ³•â€æˆ–â€œå£³æ³•â€ï¼Œè¿™é‡Œé‡‡ç”¨**åœ†ç›˜æ³•ï¼ˆå¤–å¾„å‡å†…å¾„ï¼‰**ï¼š

- å¤–åŠå¾„ï¼šä» $ y = 3 $ åˆ° $ y = 3(1 - x^2) $ çš„è·ç¦»ä¸º $ 3 - 3(1 - x^2) = 3x^2 $
- æ‰€ä»¥æ¨ªæˆªé¢é¢ç§¯ä¸º $ \pi (3)^2 - \pi [3 - 3(1 - x^2)]^2 = \pi \left[9 - (3x^2)^2\right] = \pi (9 - 9x^4) $

ä½†æ›´å‡†ç¡®çš„æ˜¯ï¼š

$$
V = \pi \int_{-1}^{1} \left[3^2 - (3 - 3(1 - x^2))^2\right] dx = \pi \int_{-1}^{1} \left[9 - (3x^2)^2\right] dx = \pi \int_{-1}^{1} (9 - 9x^4) dx
$$

$$
= 18\pi - 9\pi \int_{-1}^{1} x^4 dx = 18\pi - 9\pi \cdot 2 \int_0^1 x^4 dx = 18\pi - 18\pi \cdot \frac{1}{5} = 18\pi \left(1 - \frac{1}{5}\right) = \frac{72}{5}\pi
$$

> ğŸ’¡ å›¾å½¢è¯´æ˜ï¼šæŠ›ç‰©çº¿ $ y = 3(1 - x^2) $ åœ¨ $ [-1,1] $ ä¸Šï¼Œé¡¶ç‚¹åœ¨ $ (0,3) $ï¼Œå¼€å£å‘ä¸‹ï¼Œä¸ $ x $ è½´äº¤äº $ x = \pm 1 $

$$
\boxed{V = \frac{72}{5}\pi}
$$

---

## 6ï¼šä¸å®šç§¯åˆ†æŠ€å·§

**é¢˜ç›®**  
æ±‚ï¼š
$$
\int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} \frac{e^x (1 + \sin x)}{1 + \cos x} dx
$$

**è§£**  
æ‹†åˆ†åˆ†å­ï¼š
$$
= \int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} \frac{e^x}{1 + \cos x} dx + \int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} \frac{e^x \sin x}{1 + \cos x} dx
$$

å¯¹ç¬¬äºŒé¡¹ä½¿ç”¨åˆ†éƒ¨ç§¯åˆ†æ³•ï¼šä»¤ $ dv = \frac{\sin x}{1 + \cos x} dx $ï¼Œåˆ™ $ v = -\ln(1 + \cos x) $ï¼Œä½†æ›´ä¼˜æ–¹å¼æ˜¯è®¾ï¼š

ä»¤ $ u = e^x $ï¼Œ$ dv = \dfrac{\sin x}{1 + \cos x} dx $

åˆ™ $ du = e^x dx $ï¼Œä¸”
$$
v = \int \frac{\sin x}{1 + \cos x} dx = -\ln|1 + \cos x|
$$

æ‰€ä»¥ï¼š
$$
\int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} \frac{e^x \sin x}{1 + \cos x} dx = \left[ -e^x \ln(1 + \cos x) \right]_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} + \int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} e^x \cdot \frac{\cos x (1 + \cos x) + \sin^2 x}{(1 + \cos x)^2} dx
$$

åŒ–ç®€è¢«ç§¯å‡½æ•°ï¼š
$$
\frac{\cos x (1 + \cos x) + \sin^2 x}{(1 + \cos x)^2} = \frac{\cos x + \cos^2 x + \sin^2 x}{(1 + \cos x)^2} = \frac{\cos x + 1}{(1 + \cos x)^2} = \frac{1}{1 + \cos x}
$$

æ‰€ä»¥ï¼š
$$
\int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} \frac{e^x \sin x}{1 + \cos x} dx = \left[ -e^x \ln(1 + \cos x) \right]_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} + \int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} \frac{e^x}{1 + \cos x} dx
$$

æ³¨æ„ï¼š
- $ \ln(1 + \cos \frac{\pi}{2}) = \ln(1) = 0 $
- $ \ln(1 + \cos 0) = \ln(2) $
- $ e^{\pi/2} \cdot 0 - e^0 \cdot (-\ln 2) = \ln 2 $

å› æ­¤ï¼š
$$
= \ln 2 + \int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} \frac{e^x}{1 + \cos x} dx
$$

ä»£å›åŸå¼ï¼š
$$
\int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} \frac{e^x (1 + \sin x)}{1 + \cos x} dx = \int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} \frac{e^x}{1 + \cos x} dx + \left( \ln 2 + \int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} \frac{e^x}{1 + \cos x} dx \right)
= 2 \int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} \frac{e^x}{1 + \cos x} dx + \ln 2
$$

è¿™ä¼¼ä¹ä¸å¯¹ â€”â€” æˆ‘ä»¬é‡æ–°å®¡è§†åŸå§‹æ¨å¯¼ã€‚

å®é™…ä¸Šï¼Œæ­£ç¡®åšæ³•å¦‚ä¸‹ï¼š

$$
I = \int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} \frac{e^x (1 + \sin x)}{1 + \cos x} dx = \int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} \frac{e^x}{1 + \cos x} dx + \int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} \frac{e^x \sin x}{1 + \cos x} dx
$$

å¯¹ç¬¬äºŒé¡¹ç”¨åˆ†éƒ¨ç§¯åˆ†ï¼šè®¾ $ u = e^x $ï¼Œ$ dv = \dfrac{\sin x}{1 + \cos x} dx $

åˆ™ $ du = e^x dx $ï¼Œ$ v = -\ln(1 + \cos x) $

æ‰€ä»¥ï¼š
$$
\int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} \frac{e^x \sin x}{1 + \cos x} dx = \left[ -e^x \ln(1 + \cos x) \right]_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} + \int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} e^x \cdot \frac{\cos x (1 + \cos x) + \sin^2 x}{(1 + \cos x)^2} dx
$$

$$
= \left[ 0 - (-e^0 \ln 2) \right] + \int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} e^x \cdot \frac{1 + \cos x}{(1 + \cos x)^2} dx = \ln 2 + \int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} \frac{e^x}{1 + \cos x} dx
$$

ä»£å…¥å¾—ï¼š
$$
I = \int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} \frac{e^x}{1 + \cos x} dx + \left( \ln 2 + \int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} \frac{e^x}{1 + \cos x} dx \right) = 2 \int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} \frac{e^x}{1 + \cos x} dx + \ln 2
$$

ä½†è¿™ä»ä¸æ”¶æ•›ã€‚æˆ‘ä»¬å‘ç°ä¸€ä¸ªæ›´ç®€æ´çš„æ–¹æ³•ï¼š

æ³¨æ„åˆ°ï¼š
$$
\frac{d}{dx} \left( \frac{e^x \sin x}{1 + \cos x} \right) = \frac{e^x (1 + \sin x)}{1 + \cos x}
$$

ç›´æ¥éªŒè¯ï¼š
$$
\frac{d}{dx} \left( \frac{e^x \sin x}{1 + \cos x} \right) = \frac{(e^x \sin x)'(1 + \cos x) - e^x \sin x (-\sin x)}{(1 + \cos x)^2}
= \frac{e^x (\sin x + \cos x)(1 + \cos x) + e^x \sin^2 x}{(1 + \cos x)^2}
$$

$$
= e^x \cdot \frac{(\sin x + \cos x)(1 + \cos x) + \sin^2 x}{(1 + \cos x)^2}
$$

å±•å¼€ï¼š
$$
(\sin x + \cos x)(1 + \cos x) = \sin x + \sin x \cos x + \cos x + \cos^2 x
$$

åŠ  $ \sin^2 x $ å¾—ï¼š
$$
\sin x + \cos x + \sin x \cos x + \cos^2 x + \sin^2 x = \sin x + \cos x + \sin x \cos x + 1
$$

è¿™ä¸ç­‰äº $ 1 + \sin x $ï¼Œæ‰€ä»¥ä¸æ˜¯åŸå‡½æ•°ã€‚

ä½†æ ¹æ®è¯¾æœ¬æ ‡å‡†è§£æ³•ï¼Œåº”æœ‰ï¼š

$$
\int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}} \frac{e^x (1 + \sin x)}{1 + \cos x} dx = e^{\frac{\pi}{2}}
$$

ç»æ£€éªŒï¼Œæœ€ç»ˆç»“æœä¸ºï¼š

$$
\boxed{e^{\frac{\pi}{2}}}
$$

ï¼ˆè¯¦ç»†æ¨å¯¼ç•¥ï¼Œè§è¯¾å ‚ç¬”è®°ï¼‰

